                Since <m>d</m> cannot be negative,
                the minimum value of <m>d</m> will occur at the same point as the minimum value of <m>f(x,y)=d^2(x,y) = x^2+y^2+(6-3x-2y)^2</m>.
                Now
                <me>
                  f_x(x,y) = 2x-6(6-3x-2y) = 20x+12y-36
                </me>
