                This demonstrates that the point
                <m>\left(\frac{9}{7}, \frac{6}{7}, \frac{18}{7}\right)</m> is the point on the plane
                <m>z = 6 - 3x - 2y</m> that lies closest to the origin.
              </p>
            </li>
